The paper deals with approximation algorithms for a generalization of the Set Cover problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from game theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG) to analyze the problem. Additionally, the paper discusses LP rounding algorithms, which are commonly used in approximation algorithms and fall under the category of linear programming (cs.LG). Finally, the paper applies the results to Facility Location type problems, which are often studied in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
